"par_id3153549\n"
"help.text"
msgid "<ahelp hid=\"cui/ui/textflowpage/spinHyphenZone\">The hyphenation zone defines the maximum amount of blank space allowed at the end of a line (or added to justified lines) before Writer attempts to hyphenate the next word to improve spacing. A larger hyphenation zone creates a more uneven right margin, as fewer words are hyphenated. A smaller hyphenation zone results in a smoother right margin, as more words are hyphenated to fill the space. To reduce hyphenation, enter the length of the hyphenation zone.</ahelp>"
